add a runtime compiler test. It seems the existing compile-time tests might not give enough coverage, but they serve a purpose. I should avoid directly running macros during test compilation since that limits runtime coverage, but the functionality still needs to be tested.\\n\\nI'll need to create some helper methods like `compileSourceWithScala3`, `invokeScalaCompiler`, and `deleteRecursively`. Additionally, I'll want to include necessary imports such as `java.nio.file.Files`, `Path`, `java.util.Comparator`, and use `scala.jdk.CollectionConverters.*`. Using `Files.walk` could be a good approach.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GKq1ao7KOqUXdSglWZqq5bOv|fc_0f85615d283352ba0169fa297994ec8192952600fa2ffa3b44", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.3.6'\n    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-compiler_3:3.3.6'\n\n    testImplementation \"com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala:jsoniter-scala-macros_3:$libraryVersion\"\n", "newText": "    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.3.6'\n\n    testImplementation \"com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala:jsoniter-scala-macros_3:$libraryVersion\"\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/build.gradle\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.3.6'\\n    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-compiler_3:3.3.6'\\n\\n    testImplementation \\\"com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala:jsoniter-scala-macros_3:$libraryVersion\\\"\\n\",\"newText\":\"    implementation 'org.scala-lang:scala3-library_3:3.3.6'\\n\\n    testImplementation \\\"com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala:jsoniter-scala-macros_3:$libraryVersion\\\"\\n\"}]}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 435, "output": 1218, "cache